article.headline: SMS 63, San Francisco 42
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. (AP) -- Anthony Shavies scored 14 points to lead Southwest Missouri State to a 63-42 win over San Francisco Tuesday night in the second round of the Guardians Classic. The Bears (2-0) will play South Carolina in the tournament semifinals on Monday night in Kansas City. Selected as the tournament's wild card, San Francisco (1-1) will also advance and play Richmond in the second semifinal. The Dons were without starters James Bayless and John Cox, who were injured late in Monday night's win over Tennessee-Martin. Tommy Johnson added 12 points for Southwest Missouri and Tamarr Maclin grabbed 10 rebounds. The Bears were 7-of-18 from beyond the arc and 20-of-28 from the free-throw line. San Francisco, which shot just 36 percent from the field and went 1-of-10 from 3-point range, was led by Jovan Harris with 12 points. Tyrone Riley had 10.
